# AndisheSazan Corporate Website

> Corporate website with e-commerce section, supporting Persian and English languages, dark/light themes, admin panel, and public API.

---

## Project Introduction

This project is a corporate website with an e-commerce section, designed and implemented based on the potential needs of an organization.

The initial version was developed for a real company but was not finalized due to non-technical reasons. After that, the project was developed and improved for use in a resume and to demonstrate technical capabilities.

> **Note:** Some parts of the project are designed based on estimated needs; therefore, there may be features or structures that are not necessary or common for all organizations.

### Project History

| Phase | Description |
| :--- | :--- |
| Phase 1 | Initial development for a real organization |
| Phase 2 | Project not finalized due to non-technical reasons |
| Phase 3 | Upgrading and improving the project for resume use |
| Phase 4 | Stopping admin panel development due to lack of practical need |
| Phase 5 | Applying improvements and changes over time |

---

## Features

### Corporate Website

- Organization introduction pages, about us, team, contact, and collaborations
- Persian and English language support
- RTL / LTR support
- Dark/light theme switching capability
- Responsive design for mobile, tablet, and desktop display

### E-commerce and Content Section

- Display products with complete information and details
- Featured products showcase on the homepage
- Blog publishing and display system
- FAQ section

### Admin Panel

> **Note:** After the initial project was not finalized, the admin panel has not been further developed and may not be fully compatible with the bilingual structure of the public site.

- Product management: add, edit, and delete
- Blog management: add, edit, and delete
- FAQ management: add, edit, and delete
- Image management: upload and delete

### Security

- JWT-based authentication
- HttpOnly cookies
- Password hashing with bcrypt
- Rate limiting with express-rate-limit
- Input sanitization with escapeHtml
- Security headers with Helmet
- Application logging with Winston and Morgan
- Filtering or removal of sensitive information from logs

### Security Assessment

Some security controls of this project have been reviewed considering OWASP ASVS Level 1 requirements. However, the possibility of AI errors or not seeing some bugs by AI still exists.

